<p>Hey!</p>

<p>With our latest release, we added the option to have a fully functional forum section within your classifieds website. Please note, it is very simple to add.</p>

<p><strong>Here is how:</strong></p>

<ol>
  <li>Log in to your <strong>Admin Panel</strong></li>
  <li>Go to <strong>Settings &gt; Plugins</strong></li>
</ol>

<p><a href="//docs.yclas.com/images/forum.png" class="thumbnail gallery-item" data-gallery="">
<img src="//docs.yclas.com/images/forum.png" alt="forum section 2" /> 
</a></p>

<p><br />
3. In <strong>Forum System</strong> choose <strong>ON</strong> and press <strong>Save</strong> 
4. Go to <strong>Content &gt; Forums</strong> 
5. Press on <strong>New</strong></p>

<p><a href="//docs.yclas.com/images/forum-new.png" class="thumbnail gallery-item" data-gallery="">
<img src="//docs.yclas.com/images/forum-new.png" alt="forum section 1" /> 
</a></p>

<p><br />
6. Fill in the required fields and press <strong>Create</strong>. Once you do that you can manage forum tabs just the same way you manage categories and list them and now your users can post in the forums.</p>

:ET